title: At least five killed in 'Israeli missile strike' on Syrian capital
description: At least five people have been killed in an Israeli missile strike on Damascus, Syria's military has said.

title: US warns China that 'spy balloon' incident must 'never happen again'
description: US secretary of state Antony Blinken has met with top Chinese diplomat Wang Yi, in the first meeting between the two nations since an alleged spy balloon was shot down over America.

title: Former US president Jimmy Carter to receive hospice care at home
description: Former US president Jimmy Carter has decided to receive hospice care and "spend his remaining time at home with his family", his representatives have said.

title: Sunak shows firm determination as he vows longer-range weapons for Ukraine
description: Rishi Sunak had a hard act to follow at the Munich Security Conference.

title: Sunak says UK stands 'ready to support all allies' if they provide fighter jets to Ukraine 'now'
description: Rishi Sunak has said the UK stands "ready to support all allies if they can provide fighter jets to Ukraine now".

title: 'It is very hard': Meet Ukraine's body collectors who take fallen soldiers home
description: Dealing with death is the grimmest reality of war - something few understand better than Taras.

title: Woman 'flees kidnapper who held her against her will for nearly a year'
description: A man in the US is accused of holding a woman against her will for nearly a year before she escaped and asked for help at a petrol station.

title: North Korea fires missile into sea as South Korea and US prepare drills
description: A North Korean missile landed in the Sea of Japan this morning after Pyongyang threatened an "unprecedented" response to Western allies' rumoured military drills in the region.

title: Officials halt search for debris of three downed objects as they 'look at guts' of 'spy' balloon
description: The US and Canada have called off searches for three unidentified objects that were shot down last weekend, as investigators begin analysing the last of the debris collected from first Chinese "spy" balloon shot down at the start of the month.

title: At least 9 killed in New Zealand cyclone as PM warns figure could rise during search of cut-off communities
description: At least nine people have died following Cyclone Gabrielle, which has devastated large parts of New Zealand.

title: 'It feels natural': Hugh Jackman says it's 'inevitable' that Australia will become a republic
description: Wolverine actor Hugh Jackman has said he thinks "it's inevitable" that Australia will become a republic.

title: Body of former Newcastle United footballer Christian Atsu found following Turkey quake
description: The body of former Newcastle United footballer Christian Atsu has been found under the rubble of the building where he lived in Turkey, his agent has said.

title: How Brexit is helping European clubs beat UK giants to some top talent
description: Among the pigeons and Instagrammers of the bustling Piazza del Duomo, Cathal Heffernan has just been accosted by his first selfie-seeker since moving to Milan.

title: Kim Jong Un brings young daughter to football in sixth public appearance
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un took his daughter to a football game celebrating his late father's birthday.
